text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][inwave_infor_list style=\"style2\"][inwave_infor_list_item title=\"Accessibility\" description=\"If you have a body (you do have one of those, right?) and if you can move it even a little bit, you can start bodyweight training. These exercises are easily modified to meet any fitness level. If a move is too difficult, we can help you properly scale it back. If it is too easy, we can help you safely ramp it up. And since bodyweight exercises offer endless ways to do a little more each workout, you can always find a way to make progress.\" icon=\"database\" style=\"style2\"][inwave_infor_list_item title=\"Efficiency\" description=\"Sometime less really is more. By eliminating awkward equipment, bodyweight workouts make it easy to transition quickly from one exercise to the next. Shorter rest times means you will boost your heart rate and burn some serious calories. We call this high intensity interval training (HIIT for short). You can call it combining your cardio and strength training in one quick and effective workout.\" icon=\"dot-circle-o\" style=\"style2\"][inwave_infor_list_item title=\"Healthy body, healthy mind\" description=\"Unlike the soul sucking isolation of trudging away on a treadmill, you wont be bored in one of our fitness camps. Our group fitness approach to HIIT body weight training will help you burn fat, strengthen your core, increase flexibility and achieve better balance (yes, bodyweight training does all of those things ) and having fun with cool people elevates your mood too.\" icon=\"cubes\" style=\"style2\"][/inwave_infor_list][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"training modern\" bg_type=\"no_bg\" bg_grad=\"background: -webkit-gradient(linear, left top, left bottom, color-stop(0%, #E3E3E3));background: -moz-linear-gradient(top,#E3E3E3 0%);background: -webkit-linear-gradient(top,#E3E3E3 0%);background: -o-linear-gradient(top,#E3E3E3 0%);background: -ms-linear-gradient(top,#E3E3E3 0%);background: 